name: Nether Portal Spread
summary: Nether portals spread (nether) blocks to the overworld around the portal in a configurable radius.

name: Easy Elytra Takeoff
summary: Allows easy takeoff by elytra/colytra with a firework from the ground without an awkward jump.

name: Conduits Prevent Drowned
summary: Disables drowned zombie spawns around the player when the conduit effect is active.

name: Smaller Nether Portals
summary: Allows the creation of smaller nether portals, specifically 1x2, 1x3 and 2x2.

name: Infinite Trading
summary: Prevents villager trades from locking up, making them always available.

name: Cycle Paintings
summary: Easily cycle through placed paintings by right-clicking them with a painting in hand.

name: No Hostiles Around Campfire
summary: Prevents hostile mob spawns and burns them around the campfire in a configurable radius.

name: Just Mob Heads
summary: A minimalistic mod that adds a configurable chance for mobs to drop their heads on death. Vanilla resources only.

name: Double Doors
summary: Adds the ability for identical double doors, trapdoors and fence gates to be opened simultaneously.

name: Softer Hay Bales
summary: Makes hay bales negate fall damage entirely, Assassin's Creed style.

name: Snowballs Freeze Mobs
summary: Hitting mobs with a snowball will result in them being frozen for a configurable amount of time.

name: Healing Campfire
summary: Creates an area around the campfire where players and passive mobs receive regeneration.

name: Better Spawner Control
summary: A drag-and-drop mod which disables mob spawners whenever they are surrounded by 5 torches.

name: Just Player Heads
summary: Allows the collection of player heads via a command or death event. All heads are generated similar to a mob head via texture-data, lag free.

name: Villager Names
summary: A minimalistic mod which gives all unnamed villagers a pre-defined or custom name.

name: Village Spawn Point
summary: Sets the spawn point of a new world to the center of a village.

name: Random Bone Meal Flowers
summary: Randomizes the flowers spawned by bonemeal, allowing all (modded) types to spawn everywhere.

name: Edible Sugar
summary: Allows players to eat sugar and receive a short, configurable, speed bonus.

name: Nutritious Milk
summary: Adds a nutritious value to milk, filling up the food bar and saturation when consumed.

name: Edible Blaze Powder
summary: Allows players to eat blaze powder and receive a short, configurable, strength bonus.

name: Edible Magma Cream
summary: Allows players to eat magma cream and receive short, configurable, fire resistance.

name: Naturally Charged Creepers
summary: A minimalistic mod that allows creepers to spawn charged, both naturally and from a spawn egg in order to increase the game's difficulty.

name: Zombie Horse Spawn
summary: Allows zombie horses to spawn with a zombie riding it and other tweaks.

name: Edible Glowstone
summary: Allows players to eat glowstone dust, which causes entities around to glow with an outline.

name: Dragon Drops Elytra
summary: A minimalistic mod that makes the Ender Dragon drop an elytra on death.

name: Skeleton Horse Spawn
summary: Allows skeleton horses to spawn naturally with a skeleton riding it and other tweaks.

name: Shulker Drops Two
summary: A minimalistic configurable mod that allows Shulkers to drop two or more shells and ignore their default drop chance.

name: Automatic Doors
summary: Automatically opens doors around the player and closes them with a configurable delay.

name: Silence Mobs
summary: A minimalistic mod that adds the functionality to silence or mute a mob or villager with The Silence Stick, which can be collected by transforming a stick via the /silencestick command.

name: Pet Names
summary: Gives tamable baby animals a pre-defined name. For wolves, cats, horses, donkeys, mules and llamas.

name: GUI Clock
summary: [Client] Shows the time in the GUI/HUD with a clock in the inventory.

name: Crying Ghasts
summary: Ghasts drop their tears periodically when a player is close, giving the ability to farm them sustainably.

name: More Zombie Villagers
summary: Allows changing the default chance a zombie spawns as the villager variant.

name: Named Areas
summary: Create custom named areas/towns with a radius or by biome using signs with messages via GUI or chat.

name: Bottle Your Xp
summary: Allows the creation of experience bottles (bottles o' enchanting) from your own gathered xp.

name: Milk All The Mobs
summary: Allows sheep, llamas, pigs, donkeys, horses and mules to produce a bucket of milk.

name: End Portal Recipe
summary: Makes the end portal craftable, movable and available in survival plus other tweaks for vanilla.

name: Giant Spawn
summary: Allows giants to spawn naturally and other tweaks.

name: Villager Death Messages
summary: A minimalistic mod that broadcasts an informational death message whenever a villager passes away.

name: Stray Spawn
summary: Adds a chance for strays to spawn naturally everywhere in place of a skeleton.

name: Husk Spawn
summary: Adds a chance for husks to spawn naturally everywhere in place of a zombie.

name: Grass Seeds
summary: Allows players to use normal seeds to transform dirt into (tall) grass.

name: Spiders Produce Webs
summary: Spiders and cave spiders can periodically produce a cobweb/spiderweb when a player is close.

name: Configurable Despawn Timer
summary: Allows items to remain on the ground longer or shorter than the default lifespan.

name: Inventory Totem
summary: Makes the totem of undying effect work when it's anywhere in the inventory.

name: World Border
summary: Allows the creation of a configurable world border, limiting the world size.

name: Dismount Entity
summary: Allows players to dismount/remove/exit entities/mobs from mounted entities without breaking them.

name: Superflat World No Slimes
summary: Removes those pesky slimes when you're trying to be creative in a superflat world.

name: Always a Wither Skull
summary: A drag-and-drop mod which makes wither skeletons always drop their skull on death.

name: All Loot
summary: A minimalistic mod that has entities always drop all their possible loot in a configurable amount.

name: Despawning Eggs Hatch
summary: Allows chicken eggs on the ground to hatch safely just before they despawn.

name: Mooshroom Tweaks
summary: A 1.14+ minimalistic configurable mod that allows both red and brown mooshrooms to spawn naturally.

name: Extract Poison
summary: Allows the extraction of poison from cave spiders, pufferfish and bees with an empty bottle.

name: Move Boats
summary: Allows players to easily move boats without breaking them by holding right click.

name: Enchanting Commands
summary: Allows for easy creation of enchanted items via commands with levels above the default limit.

name: Better Beacon Placement
summary: Easily place beacon bases by right-clicking the beacon with a mineral block plus other tweaks.

name: The Vanilla Experience

attachments.description: Available by having the corresponding items in your inventory.
attachments.title: The newly added GUI Compass and Clock

summary: A light custom-coded modpack which is interchangeable with the vanilla game.

name: Grindstone Sharper Tools
summary: The grindstone (wet stone) can temporarily increase the damage of tools used on it.

name: GUI Compass
summary: [Client] Shows direction and coordinates in the GUI/HUD with a compass in the inventory.

name: Underwater Enchanting
summary: Allows the use of the enchantment table under water with maximum levels via bookshelves.

name: Sleep Sooner
summary: Adds a configurable functionality to be able to sleep a little sooner/earlier each night.

name: Zombie Villagers From Spawner
summary: Puts back the ability for zombie spawners to spawn the villager variant, removed in 1.11.

name: Move Minecarts
summary: Allows players to easily pick up and move minecarts without breaking them by holding right click.

name: TNT Breaks Bedrock
summary: Allows TNT to break bedrock. Now you've finally got easy access to the nether roof.

name: Weaker Spiderwebs
summary: Breaks spider webs/cobwebs with a configurable delay when walking through.

name: Paper Books
summary: Allows the creation of books with 9 paper.

name: Humbling Bundle
summary: A minimalistic mod that doubles all entity loot, to increase the speed of early game progress and late-game grinds. Inspired by the identically titled item in the binding of Isaac.

name: Breedable Killer Rabbit
summary: A minimalistic configurable mod which makes the killer rabbit/bunny tamable and available by breeding.

name: Fall Through Slime
summary: Slime blocks no longer support your weight when standing still, and you'll slowly fall through.

name: Mute Pistons
summary: [Client] Mutes/silences all piston sounds in the world. | silent

name: Mooshroom Spawn
summary: Adds a chance for mooshrooms to spawn naturally everywhere in place of a cow.

name: Creative Block Replacer
summary: Allows easy switching in between placing and replacing blocks in creative mode.

name: Mute Droppers and Dispensers
summary: [Client] Mutes/silences all dropper and dispenser sounds in the world. | silent

name: FAB Library
summary: The Find A Block Library assists in finding/keeping track of blocks in a world efficiently.

name: Set World Spawn Point
summary: Allows setting an exact custom spawn point for (newly) created worlds and spawn tweaks.

name: Player Tracking
summary: A 1.7 and 1.12+ PvP Mod. Allows the tracking of players via special trackers.

name: Mute Villagers
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all villagers in the world. | silent

name: Healing Soup
summary: [PvP Mod] Soup heals hearts. Adds recipes for chocolate milk, cactus soup and mushroom soup.

name: Altered Damage
summary: A minimalistic configurable mod that alters damage taken with a modifier by players and other entities. It's both possible to decrease and increase the damage.

name: Replanting Crops
summary: Automatically replants/replaces/reseeds crops harvested by using the drops. Works with wheat, carrots, potatoes, beetroots, netherwart and cocoa beans.

name: Entity Information
summary: Displays entity information on hit with the Information Stick. Useful for debugging and developing.

name: Mute Chickens
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all chickens in the world. | silent

name: Mute Withers
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all withers and their explosions in the world. | silent

name: Vote Command
summary: [Server] Adds a configurable /vote command which tells players how and where to vote.

name: Omega Mute
summary: The only and last mod you'll need to have full control over individual in-game sound.

name: Mute Cows
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all cows in the world. | silent

name: Mute Sheep
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all sheep in the world. | silent

name: Unmute Mobs
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to unmute/unsilence/restore sound to all mobs in the world.

name: Mute Pigs
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all pigs in the world. | silent

name: Bamboo Spreads
summary: Bamboo has a chance to create a new chute/sapling on a nearby block when growing.

name: Player Tracking Compass
summary: [PvP Mod] Adds a Tracking Compass, which tracks the nearest player's location on right click.

name: Mute Conduits
summary: A drag-and-drop mod to mute/silence all conduit sounds in the world. | silent

name: Passive Endermen
summary: Configurably prevent an enderman from teleporting, placing/picking up blocks (griefing) and attacking when looked at.

name: Tree Harvester
summary: Harvest trees instantly by chopping down the bottom block and automatically replace the sapling.

name: Better Conduit Placement
summary: Place conduits in front, makes placing conduit prismarine blocks easier and other tweaks.

name: Kelp Fertilizer
summary: Kelp seaweed naturally filters sea water for rich nutrients. Kelp now works like bonemeal.

name: Player Death Kick
summary: Kicks players on death with a customizable disconnect message.

name: Transcending Trident
summary: Improves the vanilla trident. Hold a water bucket to use riptide, which is more powerful.

name: Edibles
summary: Makes lots of ingredients edible, after which the player receives a short status effect. Allows eating blaze powder, glowstone dust, magma cream and sugar.

name: Extended Bone Meal
summary: Extends bonemeal behaviour. Instant grow with sneak, grow netherwart+cacti+sugarcane and other tweaks.

name: Hide Hands
summary: [Client] Hide your offhand and/or main hand in first person, optionally while holding specific items like a torch, totem of undying or a shield.
